<F P=100> Latin America &amp; Caribbean </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hu Jintao-Led CPC Delegation Ends Visit to Uruguay </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hu Jintao-Led CPC Delegation Ends Visit to Uruguay </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104020094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1533 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2104020094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Liang Rongke (4731 2837 4430)] </F>
  [Text] Montevideo, 20 Apr (XINHUA) -- A CPC delegation 
headed by Hu Jintao, member of the Political Bureau Standing 
Committee and Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee, flew out 
of here this morning for a visit to Argentina, after 
successfully concluding a two-day official goodwill visit to 
Uruguay. 
  Seeing them off at the airport were Jose Luis Puig, 
president 
of Uruguay's ruling Blanco Party; Daniel Hugo Martins, minister 
of national defense; and others. PRC Ambassador to Uruguay Xie 
Rumao also was present at the airport. 
  During his visit, Hu Jintao held successive meetings with 
Uruguayan President Lacalle, Vice President and Congress 
President Aguirre Ramirez, Blanco Party President Puig, and 
former president Sanguinetti. In addition, he also met with 
Uruguay's foreign affairs minister, economy and finance 
minister, Montevideo City mayor, Chamber of Deputies speaker, 
and other government officials and political leaders. The two 
sides briefed each other on their domestic situation and 
exchanged views on international issues of common concern and on 
further developing bilateral relations. The visit was a 
complete success for the Chinese guests, who were accorded a 
warm and friendly reception. 
  Uruguay was the first stop during the delegation's trip to 
three South American countries, which also includes Argentina 
and Brazil. 

</TEXT>

