<H3> <TI>   Hu Jintao, Delegation Arrive in Argentina </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hu Jintao, Delegation Arrive in Argentina </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2004161194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1556 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2004161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, April 20 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese 
Communist Party delegation headed by Hu Jintao, member of the 
Standing Committee of the party's Politburo, arrived here 
Wednesday [20 April] on a four-day official visit to Argentina. 
  The Chinese delegation is touring the South American country 
at the invitation of Argentina's ruling Justicialist Party. 
  Hu said in a written statement at the airport that the main 
purpose of his visit to Argentina is to "enhance friendship, 
strengthen cooperation, and promote peace and development." 
  Hu expects to exchange points of view on international and 
domestic issues of common concern and bilateral relations with 
argentine leaders. 
  The Chinese delegation was greeted by secretary general of 
the Presidency of Argentina, Eduardo Bauza, leaders of the 
Justicialist Party, and Argentine diplomats. 
  The Chinese delegation ended its two-day visit to Uruguay 
earlier Wednesday and flew to Argentina, the second leg of their 
three-nation tour of Uruguay, Argentina and Brazil. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

