<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mobile Neutron Radiography System Developed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mobile Neutron Radiography System Developed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104112394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0748 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Changchun, April 21 (XINHUA) -- A mobile neutron 
radiography system that can be applied to national defense, 
aerospace, oil prospecting, medicine and other fields has been 
developed in this capital of northeast China's Jilin Province. 
  Experts on the appraisal committee said the system marks a 
major breakthrough in China's neutron radiography technology, 
and that its critical part -- the scintillation augmentation 
screen -- is up to the top international standard. 
  China's neutron radiography applications used to be 
restricted to nuclear reactors, as its expense and inconvenience 
prevented the technology being used more widely. 
  A research group at the Northeast China Teachers' University 
took over the development work from the State Commission for 
Science and Technology six years ago. 
  The experts said the new system can take pictures with a 
sealed neutron tube as the neutron source or in a weak neutron 
current environment. The picture can be a film or a microphoto 
image processed by computer technology. 

</TEXT>

