<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Write to PLA Cadre Resettlement Forum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Write to PLA Cadre Resettlement Forum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1904223094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1046 
GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1904223094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jinan, 5 Apr (XINHUA) -- In a letter to a national 
conference on the work of resettling military cadres transferred 
to civilian sectors, which was still in progress here, Jiang 
Zemin, general secretary of the CPC Central Committee, president 
of the state, and chairman of the Central Military Commission; 
and Li Peng, premier of the State Council, expressed their 
greetings to the conference and extended cordial regards to the 
nation's vast number of former military cadres working in all 
walks of life and to comrades who made contributions to their 
resettlement. 
  The letter says: Former military cadres now working in 
civilian sectors are the country's valuable wealth and important 
force in socialist modernization. The People's Liberation Army 
is a great melting pot which has tempered and cultivated groups 
upon groups of outstanding cadres who have superior political 
standards, strong organizational and leadership ability, higher 
educational backgrounds, considerable professional skills and 
knowledge, fine workstyle, and selfless dedication. The group 
of cadres who are in the process of being transferred to 
civilian work this year will bring new vitality to economic 
construction and to other endeavors in various localities. 
  The letter says: The year 1994 is extremely crucial to the 
process of China's reform, opening up, and modernization. 
Seizing the opportunity, deepening reform, opening up wider, 
promoting development, and maintaining stability are the general 
tasks of the party and the state. Successfully resettling 
military cadres in the civilian sectors is a matter of vital 
importance to this general task and of great significance for 
promoting army building and economic construction, ensuring 
military and social stability, and promoting the smooth 
development of reform and opening up. Party committees and 
governments at all levels should take the resettlement work as 
an important political task and earnestly carry it out 
accordingly. They should do everything possible to overcome 
difficulties and successfully resettle and place every military 
cadre transferred to civilian sectors so that each has a role to 
play and each can display his talent. Comrades in the military 
should show understanding and sympathy for the difficulties of 
the localities and actively consult and closely coordinate with 
them to successfully carry out the work together. 

</TEXT>

