<H3> <TI>   Offshore Oil Industry To See `Rapid Development' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Offshore Oil Industry To See `Rapid Development' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2004145494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0743 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2004145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, April 20 (XINHUA) -- Wang Yan, general 
manager of the China National Offshore Oil Corporation (CNOOC), 
has said in Tianjin that China's offshore oil industry will see 
rapid development. 
  At a conference at the Bohai Sea Oil Corporation, he said 
that this year the output of offshore crude oil is expected to 
reach 5.5 million tons. 
  He said that in 1997, the oil output will be 12 million tons 
and the output of natural gas will be 4 billion cubic meters. 
  He said that his corporation will make full use of domestic 
and foreign funds, resources and markets so as to turn it into 
an international petroleum corporation. 
  By 1997, the corporation will have six oilfields in 
production. 
  At present, it is undertaking several infrastructure 
projects 
for opening up the oilfields, including the building of the 
Guangdong Huizhou Oil Refinery, which will be completed at the 
end of 1997. 

</TEXT>

