<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiangsu High-Tech Zones Prospering </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiangsu High-Tech Zones Prospering </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2004145194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0727 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2004145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Suzhou, April 20 (XINHUA) -- The Suzhou State 
High-Tech Development Zone in east China's Jiangsu Province has 
achieved good success, attracting increasing numbers of 
investors from at home and abroad. 
  It now has over 170 foreign-funded projects, with a total 
investment of 1.7 billion U.S. dollars. The firms are mainly 
engaged in electronics, biology, pharmaceuticals and other 
technology-intensive industries. 
  China now has a total of 52 such state-level high-tech 
zones, 
which serve as major implementation bases of the "Torch 
Program", a national high- and new-technology development 
blueprint. 
  According to the State Science and Technology Commission, 
fixed assets investment in these zones was 13 billion yuan 
(about 140 million U.S. dollars) in 1993. 
  Their development areas total over 60 sq km and nearly six 
million sq m [square meters] of floor space of buildings have 
been completed and over 12 million sq m of buildings are under 
construction. 
  The gross industrial and commercial income of the zones is 
now 57 billion yuan (about 630 million U.S. dollars), six times 
that of 1991. 
  Their export volume was over 700 million U.S. dollars last 
year. 
  By the end of last year more than 10,700 high-tech 
enterprises had been set up in the zones. Industries such as in 
optical-fiber communications and electronic information have 
become pillars of the zones. 
  Some zones have expanded from sole industrial development to 
comprehensive communities, where a service system covering 
finance, information, insurance, accounting, law, education, 
transportation, commerce and trade has emerged. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-3466 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi077_o_94007" </HT>


