<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Enterprise Asset Exchange Begins Operation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai Enterprise Asset Exchange Begins Operation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104044394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0422 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104044394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, April 21 (XINHUA) -- Altogether 220 
enterprises from 11 provinces and municipalities across the 
country have put assets up for sale at the Shanghai enterprise 
assets exchange, starting Wednesday [21 April] afternoon. 
  "This marks the founding of China's largest market in 
property rights in this, China's leading industrial center," 
said Gong Jiemin, chairman of the board of directors of the 
exchange. 
  Representatives of the first batch of 38 members, in red 
sleeveless jackets, are now busily operating an ast486-type 
micro-computer system, the set of the advanced equipment 
imported from the United States. 
  According to Gong, the enterprises with assets for sale have 
a combined property value of about two billion yuan and produce 
more than 40 varieties of goods. About one third of them are 
profitable. 
  Aiming at "high starting points, high standard and high 
efficiency" in operation, gong noted, the exchange will offer a 
centralized, fair, standard and orderly assets transfer service. 

</TEXT>

