<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangzhou Free Trade Zone Flourishing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guangzhou Free Trade Zone Flourishing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104073694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0714 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104073694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, April 21 (XINHUA) -- The Guangzhou Free 
Trade Zone is prospering since it went into operation last May, 
according to officials in charge of the zone's management. 
  By the end of March this year 263 projects set up by 
domestic 
and foreign businessmen had settled down in the zone, involving 
a total investment of 430 million U.S. dollars, 122 million 
U.S. dollars of which came from foreign investors. 
  The 1.4-sq-km zone near this capital of south China's 
Guangdong Province is one of the 13 free trade zones approved by 
the State Council to be set up across the country. 
  So far, almost all the land in the zone for financial and 
trade activities, warehouses and processing of export products 
has been sold. 
  The officials said that the zone is the first in the country 
to permit solely foreign-funded enterprises to take overall 
charge of land development and introducing projects. 
  By the end of last year the zone had put large sums of money 
into improving the zone's basic facilities, and this year, ten 
infrastructure projects will be completed or start construction 
with regard to commodity show places, quays, goods examination 
sites, electric power projects and office buildings. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

