<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shenzhen Authorities Order Foreigners To Leave </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shenzhen Authorities Order Foreigners To Leave </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2104111494 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0952 GMT 
21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2104111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shenzhen, April 21 (CNS) -- The Shenzhen municipal 
public security authorities have ordered 37 people of U.S., 
Canadian, Singaporean, Sri Lankan, Nigerian and Pakistani 
nationalities to leave China within three days. 
  The 37 persons are so-called "three-no" people, namely 
without legal certificate, a proper job and lawful residence, 
being found in lent accommodation and an "underground guest 
house" in the Luohu District of the city yesterday when the 
police conducted a sudden raid in the area. 
  These 37 people had entered the city as tourists and had not 
returned to their own countries when their tourist documents 
expired. They were instead illegally living, working, doing 
business and taking part in activities in the city, posing 
troubles to social order and the management of foreign affairs 
there. The municipal public security department imposed a fine 
on them according to foreign affairs management regulations and 
ordered them to leave the country within three days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

