<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tibet Deputy Secretary Instructs Media </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tibet Deputy Secretary Instructs Media </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104021394 Lhasa Tibet People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
1400 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2104021394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lhasa Tibet People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Text] Danzim, deputy secretary of the Tibet Autonomous 
Regional CPC Committee, pointed out at the ongoing autonomous 
regional propaganda and ideological work meeting: News media in 
Tibet should actively adapt themselves to meeting the needs of 
establishing a socialist market economic structure and do a good 
job in news propaganda and guiding public opinion. It is 
necessary to adhere to the principle of promoting unity, 
stability, vigor, and positive publicity; put the stress of news 
propaganda on economic construction, reform, and opening up; 
serve the central task--economic construction--in a more 
conscientious and effective way; and take a clear-cut stand in 
supporting and publicizing reforms. 
  Comrade Danzim said: All news media should devote their 
major energy to reporting Tibet's great undertakings of reform 
and opening up, the people's pioneering spirit during the course 
of creating a new life, and the political stability, economic 
prosperity, social progress, and happiness enjoyed by the 
people. News articles, pictures, and photographs should be 
aimed at reporting the cadres, workers, peasants, herdsmen, and 
commanders and fighters of the People's Liberation Army, public 
security police, and armed police force who are working hard on 
the forefront of economic construction, maintaining stability, 
and building the two civilizations. 
  Comrade Danzim pointed out: News propaganda should be 
designed to guide, protect, and bring into play the initiative 
of the people and of all quarters; and to make people's thinking 
and deeds conform to the party's basic line, and the general 
guidelines and tasks assigned by the Party Central Committee and 
autonomous regional party committee. News media should serve as 
a center of public opinion for promoting reform, opening up, 
economic development, and social stability in Tibet. 
  Comrade Danzim emphasized: Strengthening leadership over 
news media is of extreme importance in providing correct 
guidance for public opinion. The party committees and 
propaganda departments at all levels in Tibet should establish 
and improve the system of meeting the press. News media should 
step up contacts with economic departments. Economic 
departments should constantly keep the news media informed of 
economic work so they can promptly and accurately know the 
economic situation and report it accordingly. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

