<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Inner Mongolia Trains More Scientists, Technicians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Inner Mongolia Trains More Scientists, Technicians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2004145594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0731 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2004145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hohhot, April 20 (XINHUA) -- The Inner Mongolia 
Autonomous Region in north China has trained a large number of 
experts, indicating the formation of a multi-disciplined 
scientific and technological system. 
  In the late 1940s Inner Mongolia had not even the capability 
to produce nails or matches. 
  But since the founding of the People's Republic of China in 
1949 the central government has sent experts to help the region 
set up universities, and natural and social sciences institutes 
there. 
  By the end of last year the total number of scientists and 
experts of various disciplines was 455,000. 
  The number of experts from minority nationalities is 96,000, 
some 61 percent of the region's cadres from ethnic 
nationalities. They have achieved remarkable successes in the 
fields of veterinary science, medicine, forestry, and new 
building materials. 
  Li Donggen, a professor of the Korean nationality, has 
applied remote-sensing technology to forestry resources. 
  Xu Gorigan, a scholar of the Mongolian nationality, is now 
president of Inner Mongolia University. He produced the world's 
first test-tube goat and has made new progress in animal 
fertilization tests. He received a doctorate in Japan for 
research on techniques of external fertilization of sheep. 
  Female scientists account for almost half of the total. They 
are engaged in research into medicine, mechanics, wool spinning 
and steel making. 
  Zhang Jiahua, a professor at the Inner Mongolia Institute of 
Agriculture and Animal Husbandry, won a scientific progress 
prize for her new polyploidy beet breed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-3483 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi077_r_94003" </HT>


