<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jilin Officials Give Economic, Anticorruption Reports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jilin Officials Give Economic, Anticorruption Reports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2104060194 Changchun Jilin People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1030 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2104060194 </F>
<F P=104>  Changchun Jilin People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The ninth standing committee meeting of the eighth 
provincial people's congress held its second plenary session 
this afternoon to hear the work reports of the provincial 
government, the provincial people's court, and the provincial 
people's procuratorate. Gu Changchun, vice chairman of the 
provincial people's congress standing committee, chaired the 
session. 
  Cheng Wengui, deputy director of the provincial planning 
commission, said in his report on Jilin's commodity prices: 
Regarding Jilin's 1993 price work, aiming at establishing the 
socialist market economy system, a goal put forward at the 14th 
party congress, we gave better play to the regulatory role of 
the lever of prices in economic operation and achieved fairly 
good results. Major problems in Jilin's 1993 price work were 
that prices rose by a rather large margin, with the retail price 
index increasing by 11.3 percent in the province; and that 
collection of unwarranted fees, fines, and donations still 
occurred frequently, making the task to check this practice very 
arduous. In carrying out the price work in 1994, Jilin should 
focus on the priorities, achieve a good command of the extent, 
promote the price reform in an active and prudent manner in line 
with the capacity of the state, enterprises, and the people to 
bear the strains, gradually establish and improve the means of 
price regulation and control, and adopt resolute measures to 
strictly control price rises and stabilize the general price 
level. 
  In his report on the trial of major and serious cases by the 
courts in the process of the anticorruption struggle, Yang 
Qingxiang, president of the provincial higher people's court, 
said: From January 1993 to February 1994, the province 
registered 220 major and serious economic cases involving 235 
persons and concluded 202 cases of them, which involved 212 
persons. Of the concluded cases, 196 involved over 10,000 yuan 
each; and of the 212 criminals punished, five were cadres at and 
above the county or section level. Public trial and 
pronouncement of sentences effectively frightened economic 
criminals and enhanced the people's determination to oppose 
corruption and advocate honesty. 
  In his report on the endeavor of Jilin procuratorial organs 
to investigate and handle major and serious cases in the process 
of the anticorruption struggle, Li Xiangwu, chief procurator of 
the provincial people's procuratorate, said: From January 1993 
to the first quarter of 1994, procuratorial organs throughout 
Jilin Province accepted 3,375 economic cases on embezzlement and 
bribery and placed 2,333 on file for investigation, of which 766 
were major and serious cases, and concluded 1,654 cases. By 
handling these cases, they recovered 113.8 million yuan in 
economic losses for the state and the collective. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-3486 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi077_s_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-077 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  19 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jilin News Briefing on Anti-Corruption Efforts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jilin News Briefing on Anti-Corruption Efforts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2004034794 Changchun Jilin People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1030 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2004034794 </F>
<F P=104>  Changchun Jilin People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jilin has achieved good results in the 
anticorruption struggle for the present stage. The provincial 
procuratorate today held a news briefing to make public the 
previous work to investigate and handle major and serious cases. 
  According to statistics, Jilin placed 2,100 economic 
offenses 
and law breaches on file for investigation from August 1993 to 
March 1994. Of the total, 537 were cases on embezzlement, 193 
were cases on bribery, and 412 were cases on misuse of public 
funds. Cases involving 50,000 to 500,000 yuan totaled 229, 
those involving 500,000 to 1 million yuan totaled 12, and those 
involving more than 1 million yuan totaled nine. Cases 
involving cadres at and above the county or section level 
totaled 51. After investigation and handling of these cases, 
more than 43 million yuan of economic losses were recovered, and 
a number of major and serious cases that had created bad 
influence and repercussions were rapidly cracked. 
  When handling the cases, procuratorial organs throughout the 
province handled a number of cases committed by functionaries of 
party and government organs, especially leading cadres. One 
hundred and forty-five functionaries of party and government 
organs were implicated in the cases cracked by the procuratorial 
organs across the province from August 1993 to March 1994. (Li 
Cai), former deputy director of the Meihekou city public 
security bureau, (Chi Haijiang), director of Taonan city tax 
bureau, and other lawless persons who had violated laws while 
enforcing laws were dealt with. The procuratorial organs also 
investigated and handled 189 cases on embezzlement, bribery, and 
misuse of public funds committed by banks and other economic 
management departments, captured a number of escaping economic 
criminals, verified cheated state tax refund on exported goods 
totaling 6.84 million yuan, and recovered 3.3 million yuan of it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-3487 </DOCNO>
