<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liaoning's Shenyang's Bayuquan Harbor Project Begins Next </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liaoning's Shenyang's Bayuquan Harbor Project Begins Next </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Phase 

<F P=102>   SK1804093894 Shenyang LIAONING RIBAO in Chinese 5 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK1804093894 </F>
<F P=104>  Shenyang LIAONING RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>
BFN 

  [Text] The second phase of the Yingkou Bayuquan harbor area 
project, one of the large and medium-sized construction projects 
covered in the state's Eighth Five-Year Plan, formally started 
construction on 1 April. 
  After the completion and operation of the first phase of the 
Bayuquan harbor area project, the state approved the second 
phase in 1993 and also brought it into line with the Eighth 
Five-Year Plan. The total investment in the project's second 
phase is 367 million yuan. The second phase involves the 
construction of five 10,000- ton-class deepwater bulk and sundry 
goods berths and is expected to be completed and go into 
operation by 1997. Upon completion of the project's second 
phase, Yingkou harbor, the second largest harbor in northeast 
China, will increase 2,200,000 tons of loading and unloading 
capacity annually. 

</TEXT>

