<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC Lends Support For Toy Makers Against EU Quotas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Lends Support For Toy Makers Against EU Quotas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2104065594 Hong Kong HONGKONG STANDARD in English 21 Apr 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> HK2104065594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong HONGKONG STANDARD </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing has lent its support to Hong Kong 
manufacturers who are concerned about quota restrictions imposed 
by the European Union on toys made in China, according to 
officials of local trade organisations. A delegation led by 
Dennis Ting, chairman of the Hong Kong Toy Council and the Trade 
Development Council's toy committee, received positive feedback 
from the Chinese government during a recent visit, according to 
sources in the Federation of Hong Kong Industries. 
  "The delegation has been talking to senior Chinese officials 
including Gu Yongjiang, vice-minister of the Ministry of 
Economic and Foreign Trade," the source said. "They have been 
guaranteed by Mr Gu that support will be given by Beijing." 

</TEXT>

