<F P=100> Latin America &amp; Caribbean </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hu Jintao Meets With Uruguayan Vice President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hu Jintao Meets With Uruguayan Vice President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2004113594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1014 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2004113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Montevideo, April 19 (XINHUA) -- Uruguayan Vice 
President Gonzalo Aguirre Ramirez met with the visiting Chinese 
Communist Party delegation at the Parliament building here on 
Monday [18 April]. 
  The delegation, headed by Hu Jintao, member of the Standing 
Committee of the party's politburo, arrived here Monday at the 
invitation of Uruguay's ruling Blanco Party. 
  Aguirre, who is also president of the National Congress, 
extended his warm welcome to the delegation, saying that 
bilateral ties have seen smooth development since the 
establishment of diplomatic relations between the two countries. 
  Hu, the highest-ranking Chinese Communist Party official 
ever 
visited a Latin American nation, said the purpose of his visit 
is to promote friendship, cooperation, peace and development. 
  At the meeting, the Chinese official also hoped to further 
strengthen the friendly relations between the Chinese Communist 
Party and Uruguayan political parties and between the 
parliaments of the two countries. 
  Meanwhile, Hu had a meeting with Uruguay's former president 
Julio Maria Sanguinetti Monday and they exchanged views over 
both national and international issues of mutual concern. 
  Uruguay is the first leg of Hu's three-nation tour, which 
will also take him to Argentina and Brazil. 

</TEXT>

