<H3> <TI>   Song Jian Urges International Cooperation in High-Tech </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Song Jian Urges International Cooperation in High-Tech </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104021894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0203 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104021894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stockholm, April 20 (XINHUA) -- China wishes to 
intensify its cooperation with other countries in high 
technology, a top Chinese official told an international seminar 
on development aid policy approach to new generic technologies 
in developing countries which opened here today. 
  Song Jian, Chinese minister in charge of the State Science 
and Technology Commission, said in a speech at the seminar that 
Chinese scientists regard high technology as the key to 
development since it is a dominant factor for economic growth in 
the high-tech age. 
  Song, attending the seminar as a scientist, briefed fellow 
participants on China's potentials, development strategy and 
research and development projects in the high-tech field, reform 
of the scientific research system and achievements in the last 
decade. 
  More than 40 scientists from over 20 countries are taking 
part in the two-day seminar organized by the board of research 
and cooperation between Sweden and developing countries. 
  Some top swedish scientists expressed their wishes to 
further 
the cooperation between Sweden and China in science and 
technology when Song met with them today. 

