------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Number of draught animal-|5.551 mil                |8.2                      | 
|s/yearend                |                         |                         | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


  Good results were again achieved in fishery production; 
aquatic products totalled 364,000 tonnes in 1993, an increase of 
18.8 percent over the previous year. 
  The conditions for agricultural production continued to 
improve. At the end of 1993, the power of the province's farming 
machinery totalled 15.522 million kw, up 6.9 percent from the 
end of the year before. The number of small and walking 
tractors was 711,000 at the end of 1993, an increase of 8.7 
percent from the end of the previous year; the number of 
heavy-duty trucks was 29,000, an increase of 3.6 percent; the 
power of water draining and irrigation machinery added up to 
3.421 million kw, an increase of 4.7 percent. The total amount 
of chemical fertilizers used in 1993 (calculated in terms of 100 
percent active ingredients) amounted to 1.781 million tonnes, up 
14.2 percent from 1992. Water conservancy work was stepped up 
and the effective irrigated areas continued to increase. 
  In 1993, Anhui's rural economy continued to develop in an 
all- round manner; the output value of village and town 
enterprises reached a new level; the weight of rural industry, 
construction business, transportation industry, commercial 
activities, restaurant business, and other non-agricultural 
businesses further increased as a part of the rural economy. 
<H5>  2. Industry and Construction Business </H5>
  In 1993, Anhui took positive measures to conduct experiments 
on transforming state-owned enterprises' operating mechanisms, 
on reforming the enterprise system of property rights, and on 
building a modern enterprise system, and fruitful results were 
achieved. In the industrial sector, good development was made 
in letting state-owned enterprises and enterprises of public 
ownership be privately managed, in forming enterprise groups, in 
promoting the joint stock system on a trial basis, and in taking 
various measures to reform the enterprise system of property 
rights and the enterprise management system. Meiling Company, 
Maanshan Steel Corporation, and Wanneng Company had their shares 
successfully listed on the stock market, thereby gaining some 
experiences, further paving the way for reforming enterprise 
operating and management mechanisms, and increasing their 
vitality. The province's entire industrial economy developed 
rapidly -- the added industrial value totalled 42.9 billion yuan 
in 1993, an increase of 37 percent over the previous year and 
the highest annual growth since the policy of reform and opening 
up was implemented, accounting for 45.6 percent of the 
province's GDP. The light and heavy industry developed 
simultaneously; and the collective industry, the three kinds of 
partially or wholly foreign-owned enterprises, and other 
non-state- owned enterprises developed rapidly. 
  Production of most major industrial products increased to 
varying degrees. 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Production of Major Industrial Products                                      | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|                         |1993                     |Increase over 1992 ()   | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
