|ol                       |                         |                         | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Automobiles              |26,000 units             |130.0                    | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


  Economic efficiency improved markedly along with the 
development of industrial production. The composite efficiency 
index for the provincial industry was 95.33 in 1993. 
Constituting the index were the industrial product sales rate 
of 95.47 percent, the 11.97-percent rate of profit and tax 
generation by capital, the 5.14-percent profit rate on cost, the 
turnover rate of 1.76 times for current assets, and the overall 
labor productivity (calculated on added value) of 10,455 yuan 
per person. Nevertheless, some enterprises still suffered 
rather heavy losses, posing a need for further improvement in 
overall economic efficiency. 
  Production developed rapidly in the construction industry. 
Enterprises undertaking construction work obviously accelerated 
production along with rapid growth of investment in fixed assets 
and continual deepening of reform in the construction industry 
in 1993, turning out 5.4 billion yuan worth of value-added 
construction output, an increase of 20 percent over the previous 
year. State- owned enterprises undertaking construction work 
completed 2.199 million square meters of housing floor area with 
improved quality of work. 
  Progress was made in geological survey and prospecting. In 
1993, geological and mineral resources departments completed 
drilling and prospecting work measuring 42,000 meters in 
mechanical corer length, located two new mining sites, and 
discovered additional reserves of three minerals. They 
completed work worth 260 million yuan in monetary terms, an 
increase of 57 percent over the previous year. 
<H5>  3. Investment in Fixed Assets </H5>
  In 1993, Anhui showed a comparatively strong momentum of 
increase in investment and rationally restructured its 
investment. Total investment in fixed assets for the year came 
to 28.993 billion yuan, an increase of 34.9 percent over the 
previous year. Within this figure, investment by state-owned 
institutions and enterprises grew by 17,166 billion yuan, an 
increase of 42.6 percent; investment by institutions and 
enterprises under collective ownership 3.13 billion yuan, an 
increase of 23.3 percent; investment by individual residents 
6.666 billion yuan, an increase of 7.8 percent; and investment 
in marketable housing units of 2.031 billion yuan. Among the 
investment by state-owned institutions and enterprises, 10.026 
billion yuan were invested in capital construction, an increase 
of 40.3 percent over the previous year; 6.262 billion yuan were 
invested in renovation projects, an increase of 42.6 percent; 
and 688 million yuan were committed to other investments, an 
increase of 95.9 percent. Our investment structure was 
comparatively rational. Among the investment committed by 
state-owned institutions and enterprises in capital construction 
[as published], 11.062 billion yuan [as published] were invested 
in the secondary industry, an increase of 37.6 percent over the 
previous year. The ratio of investment in the secondary 
industry decreased from the previous year's 67.6 percent to 65.2 
percent. Among state-owned institutions' and enterprises' 
investment in capital construction [as published], 5.453 billion 
yuan were committed to the tertiary industry, an increase of 
69.6 percent. The ratio of investment in the tertiary industry 
rose from the previous year's 27 percent to 32.1 percent. 
  Investments for key construction projects were ensured. In 
1993, the state and the province invested 5.422 billion yuan -- 
or 106.2 percent of the annual plan -- in 32 key capital 
construction projects which were launched according to plan. A 
large number of technological upgrading projects and 
infrastructural projects were completed and put to use. These 
projects included the 2,500 cubic meter-blast furnace of the 
Maanshan Iron and Steel Company, the Hefei-Anqing section of the 
Hefei-Jiujiang railroad, the Hefei-Tongling highway roadbed, and 
the infrastructure of the Tongling bridge at the Chang Jiang, as 
well as the installation of the 200,000 kilowatt-generator of 
the Huaibei Power Plant and the two 125,000 kilowatt-generators 
of the Wuhu Power Plant; the operations of the Xinji, the No. 2 
Liuqiao, and the Xinzhuangzi coal mines; and the completion of 
the main structure of the Yuan Building. Progress was made in 
building the main flood control and irrigation projects along 
the Chang Jiang and the Huai He, in strengthening environmental 
protection and land management, and in improving the investment 
environment. 
<H5>  4. Communications, Postal and Telecommunications Services </H5>
  The productivity in the communications and transportation 
sector continued to grow, and a breakthrough was achieved in the 
development of postal and telecommunications services. The 
added value in this sector in 1993 was 4 billion yuan, or 23.3 
percent higher than the year before. 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
