<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gu Yongjiang Told EC `Always Supports' Reentry Into GATT </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gu Yongjiang Told EC `Always Supports' Reentry Into GATT </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204033394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0316 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2204033394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, April 21 (XINHUA) -- The European 
Community (EC) today declared that it "always supports" the 
resumption of China's status in the General Agreement on Tariffs 
and Trade (GATT). 
  The statement was made in a press release issued after a 
meeting between Christiane Scrivener, the EC commissioner for 
tariff affairs, and Gu Yongjiang, vice minister of the Chinese 
foreign trade and economic cooperation. 
  During their meeting on Wednesday, Scrivener and Gu mainly 
exchanged views on China's re-entry into GATT. 
  China, one of the founding parties of the world trade body, 
withdrew from it in 1949 and applied for re-entry in 1986. 
  Scrivener told Gu that Chinese membership in GATT is "the 
way 
China must take toward a greater participation in the world 
trade wave." 
  Therefore, the EC commissioner said, EC will support, as it 
always does, China's application for membership. 
  However, she stressed that China needs to make "very clear 
commitments" to meet some "specific conditions" put forth by 
GATT before the re-entry. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

