<H3> <TI>   Li Peng, Turkmenistan's Niyazov Discuss Bilateral Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng, Turkmenistan's Niyazov Discuss Bilateral Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104190394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1807 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ashgabat, April 21 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Premier Li 
Peng said here today that China gives priority to developing 
relations with the neighboring countries. 
  He made the remarks at a welcome banquet hosted by president 
S.A. Niyazov this evening. 
  He said China and Turkmenistan are both concentrating on 
economic construction, both in need of a long-term peaceful 
international environment. 
  "We attach great importance to the consolidation and 
development of relations with the neighboring countries, 
including Turkmenistan, and place such ties in a position of 
priority in foreign relations," Li said. 
  On bilateral ties, Li said that during this visit, China and 
Turkmenistan reached new agreement and understanding on the 
expansion of cooperation. 
  "We have every reason to believe that the friendly and 
mutually beneficial cooperation between the two countries enjoys 
broad prospects of further growth," he said. 
  Also, Li praised Turkmenistan's domestic policy, its efforts 
to explore a path of development that suits its national 
conditions, as well as its handing of relations with the 
neighboring countries. 
  China supports Turkmenistan in its efforts to safeguard 
independence and to develop economy, he said. 
  Niyazov said he agreed with Li Peng on a range of issues, 
including the expansion of bilateral cooperation, ways to 
develop economy, the safeguarding of peace and other major 
international issues. 
  He appreciated China's consistent proposition on taking 
equality and mutual benefit as a principle for handling 
international relations, which he said is also the basis for 
Turkmenistan's foreign policy. 
  Premier Li Peng is here on a three-day official visit, the 
second leg of his five-Asian-nation tour. 

</TEXT>

