<F P=103> OW2204083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ashkhabad [Ashgabat], April 22 (XINHUA) -- China and 
Turkmenistan signed another three documents on bilateral 
cooperation today, the third or last day of Chinese Premier Li 
Peng's official visit to this Central Asian country. 
  Premier Li Peng and President S. A. Niyazov attended the 
signing ceremony, which took place at the presidential palace. 
  The documents signed today include an agreement on China 
providing loans to Turkmenistan, a protocol on regular 
consultations between the foreign ministries of the two 
countries and an exchange of notes on China presenting a batch 
of materials to Turkmenistan. 
  Meanwhile, the delegation of Chinese entrepreneurs traveling 
with the premier has so far signed six letters of intent and two 
agreements with Turkmen businessmen. 
  Under one of the agreements, the China National Construction 
Engineering Corporation and Turkmenistan's Ministry of 
Construction will set up a brick-making joint venture here to 
produce 30 million bricks annually. 
  The other was signed between the China Council for the 
Promotion of International Trade and Turkmenistan's Chamber of 
Industry and Commerce for establishing cooperative ties. 

