<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Notes Yeltsin on `Stabilizing' Political Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Notes Yeltsin on `Stabilizing' Political Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104194694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1637 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 21 (XINHUA) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin told local leaders here today that the political 
situation in the country is stabilizing, according to the 
ITAR-TASS NEWS AGENCY. 
  Opening a meeting with the heads of local republics and 
regions in Moscow, the Russian president also stressed that the 
balance between the executive and legislative branches of power 
is taking shape. 
  "Much has changed in the country in the past few months, 
political stabilization is gaining strength, the disastrous 
state of dual-power has been overcome," Yeltsin pointed out. 
  "The system of meetings with the republic heads is being 
renewed," the president said, adding that approximately five to 
seven such meetings should be held a year. 
  Today's meeting is the first of its kind since the adoption 
of a new constitution and the elections for the federal 
parliament. 
  On the recent local elections in the country, Yeltsin said: 
"The elections are valid in 61 federal regions. In only 17 is 
voter turnout too low." He expressed the hope that all the 
local elections would be concluded by the end of this year. 

</TEXT>

