<H3> <TI>   DPRK Invites IAEA To Conduct Another Nuclear Inspection </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Invites IAEA To Conduct Another Nuclear Inspection </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204045594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0357 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2204045594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, April 21 (XINHUA) -- The Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea (DPRK) has invited UN nuclear inspectors to be 
present at the refueling of its main nuclear reactor, an IAEA 
spokesman said here today. 
  David Kyd, a spokesman of the International Atomic Energy 
Agency (IAEA), said the inspection this time would be "very 
important" for the UN agency to clear up allegations that the 
DPRK was developing nuclear weapons. 
  The IAEA has accepted DPRK's invitation, he added. 
  Kyd had said earlier today that the IAEA responded 
positively 
to DPRK's new offer and, provided other elements of a fresh IAEA 
inspection could be agreed upon, a new expert mission would 
leave for DPRK "before the end of this month." 
  It was reported that the fresh inspection would focus on 
DPRK's Yongbyon reactor, which was started up in 1986. 

</TEXT>

