<H3> <TI>   Egypt's Mubarak, Jiang Zemin Begin Official Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Egypt's Mubarak, Jiang Zemin Begin Official Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104104694 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1000 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2104104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The official talks between President Husni Mubarak 
and Chinese President Jiang Zemin began at the guest palace in 
Beijing today. The talks cover a number of bilateral issues and 
ways to bolster cooperation between the two countries as well as 
a number of important Arab and international issues. 
  After their talks, the two presidents will attend a ceremony 
for the signing of two agreements between Egypt and China. The 
first agreement deals with legal cooperation, including the 
extradition of criminals, implementation of sentences, and 
cooperation in the collection of evidence and investigation. 
The second agreement deals with the protection and 
encouragement of investment in the two countries. 
  The Chinese president will hold a formal dinner banquet at 
the guest palace this evening in honor of President Mubarak and 
the delegation accompanying him. 

</TEXT>

