<H3> <TI>   Forest Fire `Raging' in Inner Mongolia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Forest Fire `Raging' in Inner Mongolia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104135594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1344 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hohhot, April 21 (XINHUA) -- A forest fire which 
broke out in a lumbering site of the Hulun Buir League 
(prefecture) in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region is still 
raging on after six days concerted efforts of fighting. 
  Two fires started in the operational area six days ago. One 
was reported to have been brought under control and the other is 
still going on due to strong winds and difficult terrains. 
  Acting Premier Zhu Rongji and State Councillor Chen Junsheng 
are being kept up-to-date with reports on the firefighting. 
They have sent messages of encouragement to fire fighters via 
the regional government of Inner Mongolia and the Ministry of 
Forestry. 
  Xu Yufang, China's forestry minister and Zhu guangyao, the 
vice-minister, as well as Zhang Tingwu, vice-chairman of the 
Inner Mongolia Regional Government, are on the spot to direct 
fire fighting operations. 

</TEXT>

