<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wuhan Car Production Center Developing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wuhan Car Production Center Developing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204023994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0224 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2204023994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Wuhan, April 22 (XINHUA) -- Construction of Wuhan 
Economic and Technological Development Zone in central China's 
Hubei Province, listed as one of China's projected car 
production centers, is going ahead at full steam. 
  The development zone, approved by the State Council, is 
where 
a major Sino-French joint venture to produce 300,000 sedan cars 
will soon be launched. The zone is to focus on the development 
of businesses linked with the production of cars and automobile 
components. 
  According to local officials, Wuhan city, the provincial 
capital of Hubei, has approved the establishment of 107 projects 
in the development zone, involving a total investment of nine 
billion yuan. 
  On eight sq km of the 10 sq km development zone, ground 
leveling has been completed, said the officials. 
  The Shenlong Automobile Corporation, which was jointly set 
up 
by Dongfeng Automobile Company, headquartered in Shiyan city of 
northwestern Hubei, and the Citroen Automobile Co.,Ltd. of 
France, has decided to make an investment of 4.6 billion yuan to 
start businesses in the development zone. 
  Five big plants, with a total floor space of 260,000 sq m, 
for welding, general assembly and maintenance, for the 
Sino-French joint venture began to be constructed last year and 
are expected to be completed in 1996. 
  In addition, the Dongfeng Automobile Company has also joined 
hands with a Taiwan-based firm to jointly invest 50 million U.S. 
dollars and build a plant in the development zone for turning 
out 100,000 light-duty trucks a year. 
  Construction of basic facilities in the development zone has 
been speeded up, said the officials, adding that 23,000 sq m of 
standard workshops in the development zone have been completed 
and put on sale. 
  Moreover, construction of 11 buildings for foreign experts, 
and a school for their children, have been completed. 
  Local officials are also making concerted efforts to improve 
facilities of management and for providing services. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

