<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anhui CPPCC Provincial Committee Expands Role </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anhui CPPCC Provincial Committee Expands Role </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204030694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0245 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2204030694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hefei, April 22 (XINHUA) -- Having received 
complaints from two members of the Provincial Committee of the 
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) that 
some traffic check stations had imposed charges on passing 
vehicles at random, the Anhui provincial government issued an 
emergency circular to cancel or ban of such traffic check 
stations. 
  The provincial committee of the CPPCC has become an 
important 
source for the government of Anhui in east China to make 
decisions. 
  By the end of last month, 645 of the 653 proposals made by 
members of the first session of the seventh congress of the 
provincial committee of the CPPCC have been dealt with by the 
local government. Some 426 of the proposals were adopted. 
  The CPPCC, which consists of personnel from all walks of 
life, is a major advisory body to the Communist Party of China 
and plays an indispensable role in the country's political life. 
  Wang Rongkang, a member of the Chinese Peasants and Workers 
Democratic Party, put forward three proposals about the stable 
and sustained development of agriculture which were adopted by 
the provincial commission for agriculture and the department of 
agriculture. According to the proposals, an agricultural 
information service center and 280,000 agricultural technology 
models have been set up in the province. 
  The provincial commission for agriculture also suggested 
that 
the provincial government invest a part of its annual increased 
revenue in agriculture. 
  As to the proposals that cannot be put into practice within 
a 
short period, the government will give members clear 
explanations. 
  About 93 percent of the members of the CPPCC in Anhui are 
satisfied or basically satisfied with the handling of their 
proposals, a recent poll conducted by the CPPCC provincial 
committee showed. 

</TEXT>

