<H3> <TI>   Foreign-Funded Ventures Increase in Shandong </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign-Funded Ventures Increase in Shandong </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104192694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1529 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104192694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jinan, April 21 (XINHUA) -- The construction of 
three ventures with a total overseas investment of 608 million 
U.S. dollars started on Wednesday [20 April] in Weifang, a 
famous kite city in China's coastal Shandong province. 
  The Weifang International Industrial and Commercial Center 
and the Weifang Sunlight International Dressing Center are two 
Singapore ventures costing 280 million U.S. dollars and 28 
million U.S. dollars respectively. 
  The Weifang Xiaoyun International Industrial Development 
Garden is a solely foreign-funded venture. Invested by the 
United International Investment Corporation of the United 
States, the project involves 300 million U.S. dollars. 
  The city, benefiting from its annual international kite 
festival, has so far drawn a total of 1.5 billion U.S. dollars 
of overseas investment since it opened to the outside world in 
the early 1980s. It now has 1,346 overseas-funded enterprises. 
  Most of the investors are from Hong Kong, Singapore, the 
Republic of Korea and Taiwan. 

</TEXT>

