<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Songyuan Military Subdistrict Set Up in Jilin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Songyuan Military Subdistrict Set Up in Jilin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2204064694 Changchun JILIN RIBAO in Chinese 14 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204064694 </F>
<F P=104>  Changchun JILIN RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Yu Wenjiang (0060 2429 3068): "Songyuan </F>
Establishes Military Subdistrict"] 
  [Text] On the morning of 13 April, Jilin's Songyuan 
Military Subdistrict of the Chinese people's Liberation Army 
officially declared its establishment. By that time, all the 
eight cities and one autonomous prefecture in Jilin Province had 
established military subdistricts. Qi Lianyun, deputy commander 
of the Shenyang Military Region, and Wang Jinshan, deputy 
secretary of the Jilin Provincial party committee, attended and 
addressed the inaugural meeting. 
  According to the order of the Central Military Commission, 
Yang Baoya [2254 0202 0068) was appointed commander of the 
Songyuan Military Subdistrict, and Wu Jun [0702 6874] was 
appointed political commissar. 
  Also attending the inaugural meeting were Zhou Zaikang, 
commander, and Shi Zhaoping, political commissar of the Jilin 
Provincial Military District; Liu Shuying [0491 3219 3853], vice 
governor of Jilin; and party and government leading comrades of 
Songyuan city. 

</TEXT>

