<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sino-British Land Commission Meets in Hong Kong </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sino-British Land Commission Meets in Hong Kong </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104191094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1508 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, April 21 (XINHUA) -- The 28th meeting of 
the Sino-British Land Commission was held here today, according 
to a press release of the commission. 
  The release said the two sides agreed that the land disposal 
program for the 1994/95 financial year should amount to 117.27 
hectares. 
  The program comprises 31.01 hectares for commercial, 
residential and industrial development, and 31.43 hectares for 
home ownership scheme, sandwich class housing scheme, private 
sector participation scheme, Hong Kong housing society 
development and village housing. 
  It also includes 17.67 hectares for public utilities, 
educational, welfare, religious, recreational and other uses and 
37.16 hectares for special requirements. 
  Besides, the two sides also agreed to set aside five 
hectares 
of land in a supplementary land disposal program, the release 
added. 

</TEXT>

