<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Meets Hong Kong Businessman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Meets Hong Kong Businessman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204141094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1239 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2204141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 22 (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, a senior 
Chinese leader, told Cheng Yu Tung, chairman of the board of 
directors of the Hong Kong New World Development Co. Ltd, that 
he hopes that Mr. Cheng would more actively participate in 
governmental and political affairs and in making contacts with 
overseas people. 
  Li, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made this 
remark today while meeting Cheng, who came here to attend the 
second session of the 7th national conference of the All-China 
Federation of Industry and Commerce. 
  The chairman, also a member of the Standing Committee of the 
Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party's Central 
Committee, reaffirmed that it remains a leading policy that an 
economy of public ownership co-exists with multiple sectors of 
the economy with the former as the dominant part, which is an 
important part of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism 
with Chinese characteristics. 
  During the past few years, Cheng, also an advisor on Hong 
Kong affairs, extended his concern and support to the All-China 
Federation of Industry and Commerce, which is considered as a 
representative of non-public economic sectors in China. 
  Cheng said that he will continue his efforts to contribute 
to 
China's economic construction and Hong Kong's stability and 
prosperity. 
  Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the 
CPPCC, also attended the meeting. 

</TEXT>

