<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Egyptian President Mubarak Arrives in Beijing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Egyptian President Mubarak Arrives in Beijing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104050594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0451 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104050594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 21 (XINHUA) -- Egyptian President 
Muhammad Husni Mubarak flew in here at noon today, starting his 
three-day state visit to China. 
  Mubarak arrived for his sixth trip to China at the 
invitation 
of Chinese President Jiang Zemin. 
  Mubarak's entourage include Information Minister Muhammad 
Safwat al-Sharif, Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa and Zakaria 'Azmi, 
secretary general of the presidency. 
  Among those greeting Mubarak at the airport were Xiao Yang, 
chairman of the Chinese Government Reception Committee and 
minister of justice, Chinese Ambassador to Egypt Yang Fuchang 
and Assistant Foreign Minister Wang Changyi. 
  Egyptian Ambassador to China Samir Burhan and diplomatic 
envoys from other Arab and African countries also went to the 
airport to greet Mubarak and his party. 
  The Chinese president is expected to host a welcoming 
ceremony for President Mubarak and hold talks with him this 
afternoon. 

</TEXT>

