<H3> <TI>   Li Lanqing Views Inter-University Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Lanqing Views Inter-University Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2004155294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1517 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2004155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 20 (XINHUA) -- The authorities of 
five universities in Beijing have recently decided to cooperate 
in making use of their resources so as to improve education 
quality. 
  At a forum on cooperation between these five, Vice-Premier 
Li 
Lanqing said that the cooperation in running institutes of 
higher learning is an experiment in China's educational reforms. 
  He said it will promote the development of higher education. 
  The five universities are the University of International 
Business and Economics, Beijing Chemical Engineering Institute, 
Beijing University of Traditional Chinese Medicine and Pharmacy, 
Beijing Garment College and China Institute of Banking. 
  The five institutions are administered by different 
ministries, but they are located close to one another. 
  They have decided to jointly hire teachers, share their 
libraries, computer labs and other laboratories. 
  The students at each are being encouraged to select some 
courses at the other four. 
  The five will also jointly undertake scientific research 
programs and run some enterprises. 

</TEXT>

