<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Zou Jiahua To Visit U.S. </H4>

<F P=102> OW2104083694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0830 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104083694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 21 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier 
Zou Jiahua is to pay an official visit to the United States from 
April 27 to May 8 at the invitation of the U.S. Government. 
  The purpose of the visit is to maintain the momentum of 
high-level exchanges between the two countries, to enhance 
mutual understanding and to facilitate the bilateral 
co-operation. 
  This was announced by Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Wu 
Jianmin here this afternoon at a weekly press conference. 
  Replying to a question, Wu said that since the official 
meeting between Chinese President Jiang Zemin and U.S. 
President Bill Clinton in Seattle in the U.S. last November, 
the bilateral exchanges and contacts on various levels and in 
all fields have been on the increase. 
  During the visit, he said, Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua will 
engage in extensive contacts with U.S. leaders, government 
officials, and industry and business personages, and would 
exchange views with them on Sino-U.S. ties, Sino-U.S. economic 
cooperation and trade and other issues of common concern, in 
order to promote the improvement and development of bilateral 
relations. 

</TEXT>

