<H3> <TI>   Qiao Shi Inspects Sichuan, Stresses Reform </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qiao Shi Inspects Sichuan, Stresses Reform </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2104052794 Chengdu Sichuan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2104052794 </F>
<F P=104>  Chengdu Sichuan People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] While carrying out an inspection tour of our 
province, Qiao Shi, member of the CPC Central Committee 
Political Bureau Standing Committee and chairman of the National 
People's Congress [NPC] Standing Committee, stressed: We must 
be firm and unshakable in implementing the various CPC Central 
Committee measures for deepening reforms and soberly treat and 
solve specific problems arising in practical work. 
  Between 13 and 18 April, accompanied by provincial party 
Secretary Xie Shijie, provincial Governor Xiao Yang, Yang 
Xizong, chairman of the provincial people's congress standing 
committee, provincial party Deputy Secretary Song Baorui, and 
other comrades, Comrade Qiao Shi inspected work in Sichuan. He 
inspected medium and large state-owned enterprises and township 
and town enterprises, listening to work reports by the Sichuan 
Provincial CPC Committee and Chengdu City CPC Committee. 
  This is an important year for deepening reforms in our 
country. Qiao Shi paid close attention to the implementation of 
various measures for reforms and specific problems arising in 
practical work. He said: Since the last quarter of last year, 
more reform measures have been promulgated which carry greater 
weight. This has been an urgent demand of the situation and a 
demand for pushing forward our country's socialist 
modernizations. We must seize opportunities both at home and 
abroad which are favorable to our country's construction. Under 
the guidance of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory on building 
socialism with Chinese characteristics, we must conscientiously 
implement the spirit of the 14th National CPC Congress, and the 
Third Plenary Session of the 14th CPC Central Committee, to 
firmly and resolutely implement those reform measures which have 
been promulgated. We know that these reform measures have 
played an important role and that they have achieved initial 
results, receiving a favorable response both at home and abroad. 
Of course, to carry out extensive and profound reforms in a big 
country like ours, we are liable to encounter some problems. In 
the face of them, we must be cool-headed and calm. If those 
problems can be solved earlier, we must firmly grasp our work to 
solve them as early as possible. If some problems cannot be 
solved for the time being, we must actively create conditions to 
solve them gradually. 
  Qiao Shi pointed out: In the course of implementing the 
various reform measures, we must truly strengthen the party 
leadership. Leaders and cadres at all levels must: Be clean and 
honest and exercise self-discipline; oppose corruption and work 
hard for the people; show concern for the livelihood and work of 
the masses; lead them to overcome difficulties and solve 
problems; and they must push forward with the various 
undertakings. 
  During the inspection tour, Qiao Shi also issued important 
instructions on enterprise reforms, rural work, and so on. 

</TEXT>

