<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 25 (XINHUA) -- China today expressed 
"heartfelt congratulations" to Tsutomo Hata on his being elected 
prime minister of the new Japanese Government. 
  In response to a question from correspondents, a Foreign 
Ministry spokesman said, "We would like to express our heartfelt 
congratulations to Mr. Tsutomo Hata on his election to prime 
minister of the new government at both House of Representatives 
and House of Councillors of the Diet this afternoon." 
  "Mr. Hata is a statesman well known to the Chinese people. 
We appreciate the zeal and vision he has shown for closer 
Sino-Japanese friendship and cooperation and the tremendous 
useful efforts he has made toward this end. We are confident 
that during his tenure of office, Sino-Japanese relations will 
surely develop further on the present basis," the spokesman said. 

